# Coding Style

- Function blocks start on separate line (K&R)
- Multi-line comments, no single line from C99
- Short names for local variables
- Descriptive names when global variables are necessary
- Maximum Line width (can be exceeded if helps clarity)
  - 70 chars for source code
  - 55 chars for documentation
- Tabs for indentation, spaces for alignment
- Tab width in editors should be 8 characters
- (I put "noremap m :!make<CR>" in my .vimrc and
  enable the Makefile autorun setting for quick
  testing from inside the vim editor.)
